# Email provenance

Every outbound email from domesti-bot MUST identify **who/what sent it** and **why** (trigger), so operators can tell automatic latch mail from Settings tests, rule notifications, and SMTP probes.

## Required shape

Include a short footer line (plain text, and an equivalent HTML line) near the end of the body:

```text
Sent by: domesti-bot · <subsystem> (<trigger>)
```

Examples:

- `Sent by: domesti-bot · Vacation mode (automatic)`
- `Sent by: domesti-bot · Automations → Vacation (test email)`
- `Sent by: domesti-bot · Settings → Mail (test email)`

## Subject lines for tests

Settings / Automations **test** sends must also mark the subject (e.g. `[test]`), and the body must state that no live state was changed when that is true.

## Closed sets

When the code branches on send source (latch vs settings test, etc.), use a `StrEnum` (see `python-closed-set-enums.mdc`) rather than bare string literals.

## Do not

- Ship vague bodies such as “hysteresis window” without concrete values (users, home label + lat/lon, distance, wait duration).
- Omit provenance because the From address “already says enough” — From is the SMTP identity, not the subsystem.
